{"type":"text","timestamp":1775860854596,"sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","part":{"id":"prt_d798e26d1001eaxNNQgipOM1TJ","messageID":"msg_d798e1892001yj1vLxger22ecb","sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","type":"text","text":"I see the issue now. The `ValidatePath` function expects paths that will be joined with the workspace directory. The test is creating a file at `/tmp/.../test.txt` and passing `\"test.txt\"` as the path. However, `ValidatePath` converts `\"test.txt\"` to an absolute path which becomes the current working directory (where the test is running), not relative to the workspace.\n\nThe issue is that `ValidatePath` should **first join** the path with workDir, then validate. Let me fix this:","time":{"start":1775860854594,"end":1775860854594}}}
