{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861012635,"sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","part":{"id":"prt_d799091e90011zQK9yWiYUjnko","messageID":"msg_d799086ec0016yfDoIe67INECM","sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","type":"text","text":"I see - the test for `TestLimitedBuffer_ExceedsLimit` expects that when writing 11 bytes to a buffer with limit 5, the Write should return n=11 (accepting all input) but only storing 5 bytes. However, our implementation returns n=5 (the number of bytes actually written). Let me check what behavior is expected and also fix the test for `TestExecutor_Run_WithStdout`:","time":{"start":1775861012633,"end":1775861012633}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861020041,"sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","part":{"id":"prt_d7990989c001zzSF55GR7NWyW4","messageID":"msg_d799086ec0016yfDoIe67INECM","sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_f770facac80c4c0b80e894c2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Fix limitedBuffer to return input length","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/executor.go","newString":"func (b *limitedBuffer) Write(p []byte) (n int, err error) {\n\t// If limit is 0 or negative, accept all data\n\tif b.limit <= 0 {\n\t\tb.data = append(b.data, p...)\n\t\treturn len(p), nil\n\t}\n\t\n\tremaining := b.limit - int64(len(b.data))\n\tif remaining <= 0 {\n\t\t// Return input length to indicate all data was 'consumed' but discard excess\n\t\treturn len(p), nil\n\t}\n\tif int64(len(p)) > remaining {\n\t\tp = p[:remaining]\n\t}\n\tb.data = append(b.data, p...)\n\treturn len(p), nil\n}","oldString":"func (b *limitedBuffer) Write(p []byte) (n int, err error) {\n\t// If limit is 0 or negative, accept all data\n\tif b.limit <= 0 {\n\t\tb.data = append(b.data, p...)\n\t\treturn len(p), nil\n\t}\n\t\n\tremaining := b.limit - int64(len(b.data))\n\tif remaining <= 0 {\n\t\treturn len(p), nil\n\t}\n\tif int64(len(p)) > remaining {\n\t\tp = p[:remaining]\n\t}\n\tb.data = append(b.data, p...)\n\treturn len(p), nil\n}"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/picod.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/filesystem.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/quota.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410