{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861135088,"sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","part":{"id":"prt_d7992724c001GvYozuWFviL7Wh","messageID":"msg_d799268380015pVTl0Zn4Ap6uK","sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","type":"text","text":"The issue is that when context deadline is exceeded, `execCmd.Wait()` returns an `*exec.ExitError` first, and then the `ctx.Err()` check happens after. The exit error handling overwrites the err. Let me fix the order:","time":{"start":1775861135085,"end":1775861135085}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861148203,"sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","part":{"id":"prt_d799276f0001ZbfRxorK34A851","messageID":"msg_d799268380015pVTl0Zn4Ap6uK","sessionID":"ses_2867364a1ffeOtN07zLDlqjW0e","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_d5e67c7c08a94817bee8262a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Fix timeout error handling order","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/executor.go","newString":"\terr = execCmd.Wait()\n\tduration := time.Since(startTime)\n\n\tresult := &CommandResult{\n\t\tDuration: duration,\n\t}\n\n\tif cmd.Stdout == nil {\n\t\tresult.Stdout = stdoutBuf.Bytes()\n\t}\n\tif cmd.Stderr == nil {\n\t\tresult.Stderr = stderrBuf.Bytes()\n\t}\n\n\t// Check for timeout first before exit error\n\tif ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n\t\tresult.Timeout = true\n\t\terr = &ExecutionError{\n\t\t\tType:    ExecutionErrorTimeout,\n\t\t\tMessage: \"command timed out\",\n\t\t}\n\t} else if exitErr, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n\t\tresult.ExitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\n\t\tif status, ok := exitErr.Sys().(syscall.WaitStatus); ok {\n\t\t\tif status.Signal() == syscall.SIGKILL || status.Signal() == syscall.SIGSEGV {\n\t\t\t\tresult.OOMKilled = true\n\t\t\t\terr = &ExecutionError{\n\t\t\t\t\tType:    ExecutionErrorOOM,\n\t\t\t\t\tMessage: \"process killed due to OOM\",\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t} else if err == nil {\n\t\tresult.ExitCode = 0\n\t} else if ctx.Err() == context.Canceled {\n\t\terr = &ExecutionError{\n\t\t\tType:    ExecutionErrorCancelled,\n\t\t\tMessage: \"command was cancelled\",\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn result, err","oldString":"\terr = execCmd.Wait()\n\tduration := time.Since(startTime)\n\n\tresult := &CommandResult{\n\t\tDuration: duration,\n\t}\n\n\tif cmd.Stdout == nil {\n\t\tresult.Stdout = stdoutBuf.Bytes()\n\t}\n\tif cmd.Stderr == nil {\n\t\tresult.Stderr = stderrBuf.Bytes()\n\t}\n\n\tif ctx.Err() == 